ystem. This energy shift is increased when\nincluding the D-state contribution. We also study the expected dependence of\nthe D-state effects on the separation energy and orbital angular momentum of\nthe transferred nucleon. Their influence on the spectroscopic information\nextracted from (d,p) reactions is quantified for a particular case of\nastrophysical significance.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 20 Jan 2017 16:53:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-03-08"}
