, leading to the appearance of amorphous-like behavior\nand a broadening of up to three orders of magnitude for the homogeneous\nlinewidth even when low-energy grinding methods are employed. Annealing at high\ntemperatures can improve the properties in some samples, with homogeneous\nlinewidths reduced to less than 10 kHz, approaching the bulk crystal linewidth\nof 3 kHz under the same experimental conditions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 20 Jan 2017 19:02:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-08-03"}
